Birmingham, Wolves Tie 1-1 in Premier League; Liverpool Beats Newcastle

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-05-01T13:20:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/birmingham-wolves-tie-1-1-in-premier-league-liverpool-beats-newcastle.html
Wolverhampton Wanderers  remain in the
relegation positions in English soccer’s Premier League after a
1-1 tie at 10-man Birmingham City today. Liverpool defeated
Newcastle 3-0 to climb to fifth spot.  Wolves, who could have climbed out of the three-team drop
zone with a win, took a seventh-minute lead at St. Andrew’s on a
penalty from Steven Fletcher. Sebastian Larsson replied on 27
minutes for the Blues, who played more than half the match with
10 men following a 38th-minute red card for Craig Gardner.  Last-place West Ham can move to 17th with a win at
Manchester City later today. The Hammers have 32 points, Wolves
34, 18th-place Wigan and Blackpool, in 17th, are on 35 and
Blackburn 38. Birmingham has 39 points.  At the top of the standings, first-place  Manchester United 
can move six points clear of Chelsea if it defeats Arsenal
today. United has 73 points, Chelsea 70, Arsenal 64 and
Manchester City 59, with Liverpool and Tottenham on 55.  Maxi Rodriguez,  Dirk Kuyt , with a penalty kick, and Luis Suarez scored at Anfield for Liverpool.  Yesterday, Chelsea beat Tottenham 2-1, Blackburn defeated
Bolton 1-0, Blackpool tied 0-0 against Stoke, while Wigan drew
1-1 against Everton. Fulham won 3-0 at Sunderland, and West
Bromwich Albion defeated Aston Villa 2-1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in London at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 